16/12/2003
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Prime Minister Tony Blair and his Greek counterpart Costas Simitis met on Monday (15 December). 
Simitis described the capture of former Iraqi ruler Saddam Hussein as a positive development that will contribute to stability in the country and region. 
As for last week's EU summit in Brussels, he stressed the need for EU member states to overcome differences related to the European Constitution and move towards formal adoption. 
He also called on Turkey to exert greater pressure to resolve the dispute in Cyprus. 
Blair said he was willing to press both sides. 
(MPA, ANA - 15/12/03)
